methods.name: eval
methods.description:
Runs a string of Javascript code
 Don't abuse this!

methods.name: load
methods.description: Loads and external file containing code

methods.name: shareImage
methods.description: Share Image with an app installed in the system

methods.name: shareText
methods.description: Share text with an app installed in the system

methods.name: runOnUiThread
methods.description: Runs a function in the UI thread. This is normally not needed but might be required when combined with Threads

methods.name: liveCodingOverlay
methods.description: Shows a feedback overlay with the live-executed code

methods.name: sendEvent
methods.description: Sends a name event with a json object

methods.name: listenEvent
methods.description: Receives a named event with a json object

methods.name: removeEvent
methods.description: Receives a named event with a json object

methods.name: openFileWithApp
methods.description: Try to open a file with an app installed in the system

methods.name: onCreate
methods.description: Callback called when script is loaded

methods.name: onPause
methods.description: Callback called when script is paused. For example when switching to a different task.

methods.name: onResume
methods.description: Callback called when script is resumed. This can be called either when the app loads for the first time or switches back from a different app.

methods.name: onDestroy
methods.description: Callback called when script is closed

methods.name: log
methods.description: Shows any text in the WebIDE console

methods.name: error
methods.description: Shows any text in the WebIDE console

methods.name: positionMode
methods.description:
Changes the position mode.
 By default, Protocoder places the widgets using normalized coordinates (0 to 1)
 Sometimes we need a bit more control on how to create layouts so we can specify that the
 views will lay out using pixel or dp (density independent pixels) units

methods.name: removeAllViews
methods.description: Remove all views in the layout

methods.name: allowScroll
methods.description:
Allows the main interface to scroll up and down.
 It's quite handy to lay out many widgets that cannot fit in a screen.

methods.name: background
methods.description: Changes the background color using Hexadecimal color

methods.name: newViewPager
methods.description: Creates a pager that contain slidable views

methods.name: addSlider
methods.description: Adds a slider. By default the range is [0, 1].

methods.name: addMatrix
methods.description: Adds a matrix with M and N size. Useful when creating step sequencers and similar.

methods.name: newProgress
methods.description: Creates a progress bar of n units

methods.name: add
methods.description: Adds a view created with new (newButton, newToggle, etc)

methods.name: addPlot
methods.description: Adds a plot, by default the range is [0, 1]

methods.name: addMap
methods.description: Adds a map widget using OpenStreetMap

methods.name: addProcessingCanvas
methods.description:
Adds a processing view.
 This Processing view acts quite similar to Processing.org for Android. In fact is the same, although
 some things work a bit differently to play well with the rest of the framework.

 - All the Processing functions prepend the Processing (p) object.
 p.fill(255); p.stroke(); p.rect();

methods.name: showWeb
methods.description:
Shows a web in a different screen.
 Once the web is opened, we loose the control of the script

methods.name: resize
methods.description: Resize a view to a given width and height. If a parameter is -1 then that dimension is not changed

methods.name: onTouches
methods.description: Attach callback to a view that will output multitouch events

methods.name: takeViewScreenshot
methods.description: Takes a screenshot of a view in a Bitmap form

methods.name: onKeyDown
methods.description: Tells which software / hardware / gamepad button is pressed

methods.name: onKeyUp
methods.description: Tells which software / hardware / gamepad button is released

methods.name: onKeyEvent
methods.description: Gives a key event when of a software / hardware / gamepad button

methods.name: smsSend
methods.description:
Sends a SMS to a given phone number.
 Please, be careful, since this method might cost you MONEY depending on your phone plan!

methods.name: onSmsReceived
methods.description: This method will be triggered when an SMS is received

methods.name: isScreenOn
methods.description: Check if the screen is on

methods.name: isAirplaneMode
methods.description: Check if the device is in airplane mode

methods.name: wakeLock
methods.description: Prevent the device suspend at any time. Good for long living operations

methods.name: openEmailApp
methods.description:
Creates a new mail using the default e-mail app.
 Note: It won't be automatically send

methods.name: openDial
methods.description: Open the system's phone dial screen

methods.name: call
methods.description: Call a given phone number using the device's call manager

methods.name: openWebApp
methods.description: Open the default web browser with a given Url

methods.name: openWebSearch
methods.description: Open the search app with the given text

methods.name: copyToClipboard
methods.description: Copy a given text into the clipboard.

methods.name: getFromClipboard
methods.description: Get the content from the clipboard

methods.name: battery
methods.description: Get the current device battery level

methods.name: onNewNotification
methods.description:
Gets notifications from other apps.
 In order to work to must enable the access of notifications in your device settings

methods.name: listInstalledApps
methods.description: Loads the list of installed applications in mApplications.
